HEADWORD: Discubitory
<hw>Dis*cu"bi*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>discumbere</ets>, <ets>discubitum</ets>, to lie down, recline at
table; <ets>dis-</ets> + <ets>cumbere</ets> (in comp.) to lie
down.]</ety> <def>Leaning; fitted for a reclining posture.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

